did.abstract: The Historic Photograph Subject File contains photographs taken throughout the Pacific Northwest and Alaska that cover a wide variety of subjects.

scopecontent.p: The Historic Photograph Subject File contains photographs taken throughout the Pacific Northwest and Alaska that cover a wide variety of subjects.

arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into 25 series based on general subject areas.

accessrestrict.p: This collection is open and available for research use.

prefercite.p: Historic Photograph Subject File, circa 19th century-20th century (PC 2)
Manuscripts, Archives, and Special Collections, Washington State University Libraries, Pullman, WA.

acqinfo.p: This collection started with a core of photographs taken during the 1930s as part of the Federal Writers Project for the production on the American Guide. Subsequently, the Historic Photograph Subject File was expanded through gifts and some purchases.

processinfo.p: Stacee Sager and Trevor Bond, Special Collections Librarian, created this guide in 2001.

controlaccess.p: This collection is indexed under the following headings in the online catalog. Researchers desiring materials about related topics, persons, or places should search the catalog using these headings.
